prediction Transformation

The prediction transformation produces an Einstein Discovery prediction for a dataset. Einstein Discovery uses predictive analytics, which analyzes historical data (based on data mining, machine learning, and predictive statistical modeling) to identify patterns and predict future outcomes.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSIONS
NEEDED
To add a prediction node to a dataflow: View Einstein Discovery Recommendations permission
To view predictions: View Einstein Discovery Recommendations permission

After you create an Einstein Discovery model, the prediction transformation uses the trained model to make predictions on your data. The transformation outputs a new column with the predicted values.

prediction Transformation Parameters in the Dataflow JSON

PARAMETER REQUIRED? VALUE
predictionDefinitionName Yes Name of the prediction definition to use.
predictionColumnName Yes Name of the new dataset column to contain the score.
predictionColumnLabel Yes UI label of the new dataset column to contain the score.

EXAMPLE
{
  "Customers": {
    "action": "edgemart",
    "parameters": {
      "alias": "Customers"
    },
    ...
  }
}
